EverQuest II is the long-awaited sequel to EverQuest.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Long awaited? Who asked for this? I was just starting to enjoy EQ1! </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Is EQII an expansion of the original EverQuest?<br>
EverQuest II is not an expansion, but rather a sequel that continues the ongoing history of Norrath and its inhabitants. EQII will introduce a number of features that have never been utilized in massively multiplayer games.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Duh. We saw the II at the end.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
When will EQII be released?<br>
Our anticipated launch date is 4th Quarter 2003. <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>So expect it out by the time we retire.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Will a monthly fee be required to play?<br>
Yes, a monthly fee will be required. However, the exact cost has not been determined at this time.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>We need to fund the new game so we can consistantly screw it up, sorta like in EQ1. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
How will EQII differ from other massively multiplayer games?<br>
At the time of launch, the EQII team will have over four years of massively multiplayer gaming experience to build upon. Our plans for the combat, quest and spell systems, just to name a few, along with our new 3D engine, will bring massively multiplayer gaming to new heights.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The same idiots who stumbled through the development of EQ1 are back. We hope they learned something. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Once I subscribe, should I expect new content be added to the game?<br>
Absolutely. A dedicated team of quest and content designers will be acquired prior to launch. Assembling the content team early is necessary to assure a steady flow of quests and content into the game world. <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This means they have no plan. At the last minute they will hire some old Half-Life mod builders and tell them “ok guys, make some magic” </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Is the same development team that created EverQuest the creators of EQII?<br>
A number of key original team members make up a portion of the EverQuest II team. With the size and scope of the EQII project, it was necessary to expand the team from its original size.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This means they have fresh new morons to compliment the old worn out ones. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
What are the game's requirements?<br>
Operating System: Windows 98/2000/ME/XP <br>
Processor: 733 mhz<br>
RAM: 512 MB<br>
Video Card: DirectX 8 compliant. Pixel shader and Vertex shader compatible hardware with 64mb of texture memory (eg: GeForce 3)<br>
Sound Card: DirectSound compatible audio hardware<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Intel, AMD, Creativelabs, NVIDA and various other hardware companies are crapping their pants in anticipation.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
How do I become a beta tester?<br>
Information regarding the EverQuest II beta test will be made available on the official website. However, it is important to note that many of our Legends subscribers will be the first to experience EverQuest II in its beta. We will be giving preference to longtime Legends Subscribers, so our suggestion is that if you're interested in EverQuest Legends, sign up now. After Legends players, longtime EQ subscribers will be eligible for a phase of the beta as well. We realize this information is somewhat vague, and the only reason for that is we don't have an exact date yet.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Another reason why Legends sucks.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
What is the goal of the game?<br>
The primary of goal of EQII is to create and advance a unique role-playing persona within the world of Norrath. This may be accomplished a number of ways, including solving mysterious quests, slaying vicious monsters and crafting powerful relics.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Isn’t this the goal of EVERY OTHER RPG EVER MADE? </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
How do I communicate with other players?<br>
Communication will take place within the UI chat window(s).<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>As opposed to just thinking really hard and hoping your guild will hear you. We can assume it will involve words of some sort. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
What if I don't have a lot of time to play? Will the game still be fun for someone like me?<br>
One of the main focuses for EverQuest II is to design methods of gameplay that will facilitate both casual and hardcore players. <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Which means the game will get boring after the first week. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Can I customize my character's appearance?<br>
Yes. Players will be able to customize both the character's body and face, as well as their appearance through the equipping of specialized weapons, armor and items.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Unlike in EQ, where we picked a face and body, then got equipment to make us look different. Hey wait… </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Can I transfer my characters that I created in the original EQ to EQII?<br>
Existing EverQuest characters will not be transferred to EQII.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This means they hope we will play both and pay them more money.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
What 3D engine will EQII use?<br>
EverQuest II utilizes a proprietary 3D engine, which was developed in-house by the EQII programming team. The EQII engine takes full advantage of current cutting edge 3D hardware, as well as future hardware technology.<br>
